(Constable Oh Se Hoon)

86
00:09:03,379 --> 00:09:05,379
(Constable Oh Se Hoon)

87
00:09:16,629 --> 00:09:21,200
(Word Puzzle)

88
00:09:22,299 --> 00:09:24,100
He's learning very quickly,

89
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:25,799
and he still has his habits.

90
00:09:26,470 --> 00:09:28,870
Then why won't he speak?

91
00:09:30,309 --> 00:09:32,480
He's probably going through
an identity crisis.

92
00:09:33,039 --> 00:09:34,610
He needs time to adjust.

93
00:09:37,110 --> 00:09:38,750
You may be offended,

94
00:09:39,649 --> 00:09:43,250
but from a researcher's perspective,
this is a fascinating case.

95
00:09:44,990 --> 00:09:47,120
But of course,
we'll do our best to help him.

96
00:09:48,429 --> 00:09:49,559
Thank you.

97
00:09:51,799 --> 00:09:54,029
(Sweet chocolate)

98
00:10:03,509 --> 00:10:05,279
("The 'Executioner' Dies
While in Police Custody")

99
00:10:05,279 --> 00:10:07,379
Despite being murdered
while in police custody,

100
00:10:07,379 --> 00:10:10,509
the police have failed
to identify the killer...

101
00:10:10,509 --> 00:10:13,750
or find any leads.

102
00:10:13,990 --> 00:10:16,220
The late Jin Jae Gyu was suspected
of being the Executioner...

103
00:10:16,220 --> 00:10:20,059
who committed the serial killings
that happened 20 years ago.

104
00:10:20,059 --> 00:10:22,789
He had harmed himself yesterday
in court...

105
00:10:22,789 --> 00:10:23,860
while his warrant
was being verified.

106
00:10:23,860 --> 00:10:25,830
While admitted to hospital,
he lost his life.

107
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,629
There have only been speculations
that he had murdered six victims,

108
00:10:28,629 --> 00:10:31,769
including Park Gi Dan,
the cult leader,

109
00:10:31,769 --> 00:10:34,210
and Cho Sung Dong,
the former president of TBC.

110
00:10:34,269 --> 00:10:36,509
There has been no solid evidence
to support this.

111
00:10:36,639 --> 00:10:38,740
The killer,
who's also known as the Eraser,

112
00:10:38,740 --> 00:10:41,950
was once suspected
of being Jin's accomplice.

113
00:10:41,950 --> 00:10:43,879
But after Jin was murdered,

114
00:10:43,879 --> 00:10:48,820
the police have become
baffled by this case.

115
00:10:48,820 --> 00:10:50,889
According to a tip-off
we have received,

116
00:10:51,159 --> 00:10:55,460
Det. Dong was at the scene
when Jin was murdered.

117
00:10:55,789 --> 00:10:58,330
A high-ranking police official...

118
00:10:58,330 --> 00:11:01,399
Jin Jae Gyu was murdered
in front of the police...

119
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:03,769
while he was in their custody.

120
00:11:03,899 --> 00:11:05,799
During a press conference
this morning,

121
00:11:05,799 --> 00:11:07,970
the police have perplexed
the reporters...

122
00:11:08,110 --> 00:11:12,679
by saying that Jin's murderer,
the Eraser, could have superpowers.

123
00:11:12,909 --> 00:11:14,309
But two hours later,

124
00:11:14,309 --> 00:11:15,980
- they said nothing was for certain.
- Superpowers?

125
00:11:15,980 --> 00:11:17,620
I knew it.

126
00:11:17,620 --> 00:11:20,080
Did they go back on their words
once again?

127
00:11:20,250 --> 00:11:21,450
How many times has it been?

128
00:11:21,549 --> 00:11:23,620
I'd be surprised if they end up
catching the killer.

129
00:11:23,620 --> 00:11:25,720
The public is outraged...

130
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:27,120
and have blamed the police...

131
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:29,860
for the victims' deaths.

132
00:11:30,059 --> 00:11:31,659
Hundreds of thousands of people...

133
00:11:31,659 --> 00:11:33,700
- I knew it.
- Me too.

134
00:11:46,980 --> 00:11:48,110
Did you get
the search and seizure warrant?

135
00:11:48,110 --> 00:11:49,980
- Is this because of Jin's death?
- Whom are you searching?

136
00:11:49,980 --> 00:11:52,049
- Is it the RIU?
- Which office are you from?

137
00:11:52,049 --> 00:11:53,820
- Northern Prosecutor's Office?
- The Special Investigation Team?

138
00:11:53,820 --> 00:11:55,549
- Whom are you searching?
- Move aside.

139
00:11:55,549 --> 00:11:57,389
- Move!
- Please comment!

140
00:11:57,389 --> 00:11:58,720
- Please!
- Tell us!

141
00:12:07,429 --> 00:12:10,169
(Regional Investigation Unit)

142
00:12:11,470 --> 00:12:12,539
Stop what you're doing!

143
00:12:13,570 --> 00:12:16,570
Take your hands off of your desk
right now.

144
00:12:16,740 --> 00:12:19,110
Stay still. Hey, hey!

145
00:12:19,110 --> 00:12:20,240
Don't touch anything!

146
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:22,379
Sit down. Hey, hey!

147
00:12:25,980 --> 00:12:27,049
What's going on?

148
00:12:27,149 --> 00:12:28,990
What do you think?
It's a search and seizure.

149
00:12:28,990 --> 00:12:30,019
What?

150
00:12:31,419 --> 00:12:33,090
Touch a single piece of paper,

151
00:12:33,090 --> 00:12:34,330
and you'll be charged
for concealing evidence.

152
00:12:34,330 --> 00:12:36,730
Everyone, step away
from your desks right now.

153
00:12:36,730 --> 00:12:39,059
- Mind your manners.
- Don't be absurd.

154
00:12:39,059 --> 00:12:40,799
- What? Let me go.
- Come on.

155
00:12:40,970 --> 00:12:42,269
Your position doesn't give you
the right to treat us this way.

156
00:12:42,269 --> 00:12:45,039
You better behave
in front of the chief prosecutor.

157
00:12:45,139 --> 00:12:47,070
He should know better than to abuse
his power in this day and age.

158
00:12:54,649 --> 00:12:55,649
(Search and Seizure Warrant)

159
00:12:56,149 --> 00:12:57,210
You were here, after all.

160
00:12:59,950 --> 00:13:01,750
Why are your men so impudent?

161
00:13:02,049 --> 00:13:03,450
Just do what you're here to do
and leave.

162
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,820
You're responsible for this.

163
00:13:05,919 --> 00:13:07,690
You're the reason why
Jin Jae Gyu died.

164
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:10,629
- Then arrest me.
- That's not a bad idea.

165
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,970
You do remember
that I warned you, right?

166
00:13:15,370 --> 00:13:16,529
What are you doing?

167
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:20,100
Hello, Deputy Chief Lee Shin Woong.

168
00:13:22,769 --> 00:13:23,809
We finally get to meet.

169
00:13:24,539 --> 00:13:26,909
What brings you here,
Chief Prosecutor Woo Seok Do?

170
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:29,350
I feel greatly honored...

171
00:13:29,980 --> 00:13:31,950
to be recognized after being
looked down upon...

172
00:13:31,950 --> 00:13:33,580
by a bunch of small fry.

173
00:13:34,789 --> 00:13:37,450
Of course. You'll be the next
Public Prosecutor General.

174
00:13:37,590 --> 00:13:38,789
You were promoted and transferred...

175
00:13:38,789 --> 00:13:39,990
to Central District
Prosecutor's Office.

176
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:42,460
Amidst
District Attorney Lim's scandal,

177
00:13:42,460 --> 00:13:44,200
you remained safe and sound.

178
00:13:46,629 --> 00:13:48,700
I forgot to bring your warrant.

179
00:13:49,129 --> 00:13:50,470
- Mr. Kim.
- Yes, sir.

180
00:13:50,629 --> 00:13:52,000
Go to the court
and request another warrant.

181
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,000
I'd like to search
the deputy chief's office.

182
00:13:54,340 --> 00:13:55,470
What are you doing?

183
00:13:56,370 --> 00:13:58,940
- Shall we talk in my office?
- Why? Are you scared?

184
00:13:58,940 --> 00:14:01,480
How dare you talk like that to...

185
00:14:02,809 --> 00:14:05,049
I do respect how determined you are.

186
00:14:06,279 --> 00:14:07,750
But you should be more dignified.

187
00:14:07,750 --> 00:14:11,289
The prosecution doesn't care
about showing dignity...

188
00:14:11,289 --> 00:14:12,960
in front of you, suspects.

189
00:14:13,690 --> 00:14:15,990
Sir, you shouldn't deal
with someone as lowly as him.

190
00:14:16,059 --> 00:14:17,830
- "Lowly"?
- I'd like to make a bet...

191
00:14:18,399 --> 00:14:20,460
that you'll leave empty-handed...

192
00:14:20,460 --> 00:14:21,529
Are you trying to be funny?

193
00:14:23,070 --> 00:14:25,740
I heard that you were present...

194
00:14:26,039 --> 00:14:28,909
during Detective Dong's arrest.

195
00:14:30,610 --> 00:14:32,240
- Move aside!
- Wait!

196
00:14:32,679 --> 00:14:34,250
- We have no time for...
- Gosh.

197
00:14:34,980 --> 00:14:35,980
So what?

198
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:39,980
I'm sure you know
what the problem is.

199
00:14:40,350 --> 00:14:41,590
Beats me.

200
00:14:41,950 --> 00:14:44,149
I won't hold you responsible for it
if you leave.

201
00:14:44,149 --> 00:14:45,789
I'm afraid I can't do that.

202
00:14:45,889 --> 00:14:47,860
Send him the documents
that he needs later.

203
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:50,429
- Yes, sir.
- You're quite humorous.

204
00:14:50,629 --> 00:14:51,929
So you'll take responsibility,
is that it?

205
00:14:54,799 --> 00:14:56,299
You assaulted a suspect.

206
00:14:56,299 --> 00:14:58,970
(Assaulting a suspect could result
in up to 5 years in jail.)

207
00:14:58,970 --> 00:15:00,169
Do you have proof?

208
00:15:00,870 --> 00:15:02,009
Shall we bet?

209
00:15:02,169 --> 00:15:04,909
Let's see if I'm just bluffing
without any evidence...

210
00:15:05,639 --> 00:15:08,610
or if I have a high-resolution video
to prove it.

211
00:15:08,809 --> 00:15:10,480
I doubt that you have one.

212
00:15:12,820 --> 00:15:14,590
But even if you do,
it won't work against me.

213
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:19,460
You're right.
Prosecutors are the only ones...

214
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:21,090
who have the right
to indict an individual.

215
00:15:21,629 --> 00:15:25,600
But if that video
were to be aired on the news,

216
00:15:27,559 --> 00:15:29,029
you may not be indicted,

217
00:15:29,529 --> 00:15:31,269
but you'll have to step down.

218
00:15:31,639 --> 00:15:32,940
We all know
that scandalous prosecutors...

219
00:15:33,639 --> 00:15:37,169
always end up
opening their own practice.

220
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:40,009
Are you challenging me?

221
00:15:41,450 --> 00:15:42,649
Let's make a bet...

222
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:45,649
whether you'll leave quietly...

223
00:15:46,679 --> 00:15:49,820
or put up a fight.

224
00:16:02,070 --> 00:16:03,200
Let's pull out.

225
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:04,639
Sir?

226
00:16:06,470 --> 00:16:08,610
- Pack it up.
- Yes, sir.

227
00:16:11,940 --> 00:16:14,379
The rumors about you were right.

228
00:16:16,379 --> 00:16:18,580
We'll be seeing each other soon.

229
00:16:33,100 --> 00:16:34,100
I'm sorry.

230
00:16:34,629 --> 00:16:36,000
Hand in your resignation letter...

231
00:16:36,370 --> 00:16:37,970
and go to the Prosecutors' Office.

232
00:16:38,740 --> 00:16:41,309
I will, but please give me
a week to investigate.

233
00:16:41,309 --> 00:16:43,070
- Even four days will be...
- Han Sun Mi.

234
00:16:44,940 --> 00:16:46,309
- Yes, sir.
- Do you know...

235
00:16:46,309 --> 00:16:48,649
the number-one reason why soldiers
die the most on the battlefield?

236
00:16:51,679 --> 00:16:53,220
It's because of foolish leaders...

237
00:16:54,519 --> 00:16:55,950
like you.

238
00:16:57,350 --> 00:16:59,960
The RIU was humiliated
thanks to you.

239
00:16:59,990 --> 00:17:01,789
No, the entire police force
was humiliated.

240
00:17:02,190 --> 00:17:03,860
And yet, you still want to continue?

241
00:17:05,299 --> 00:17:06,829
You'll still be a lawyer
even if you step down,

242
00:17:06,829 --> 00:17:08,329
but that's not the case
for the others.

243
00:17:09,329 --> 00:17:13,099
It's my duty to help them
feed their families.

244
00:17:16,470 --> 00:17:18,240
If you still refuse to let go,

245
00:17:18,809 --> 00:17:21,150
Young Soo will get fired as well.
Is that what you want?

246
00:17:21,410 --> 00:17:22,480
No, sir.

247
00:17:22,650 --> 00:17:24,309
Then do...

248
00:17:25,079 --> 00:17:26,319
what's right.

249
00:19:12,490 --> 00:19:13,589
You're late.

250
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:21,099
You read my passcode?

251
00:19:22,799 --> 00:19:24,640
What else did you read
from my memory?

252
00:19:25,869 --> 00:19:27,339
What do you take me for?

253
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:29,710
The four keys were covered
with your prints.

254
00:19:30,369 --> 00:19:32,140
What kind of a profiler
is this clumsy?

255
00:19:34,140 --> 00:19:35,980
Stop frowning, will you?

256
00:19:36,450 --> 00:19:38,549
I was just worried
that the Eraser would come for you.

257
00:19:39,150 --> 00:19:42,289
The moment I die,
everyone will know who he is.

258
00:19:43,519 --> 00:19:45,059
If you feel reassured,
you may leave.

259
00:19:45,859 --> 00:19:46,990
I have nowhere to go.

260
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:48,190
Woo Seok Do is searching for me,

261
00:19:48,190 --> 00:19:50,230
so his men are waiting at my house
and in front of hotels.

262
00:19:53,460 --> 00:19:54,900
The killer murdered my mother.

263
00:20:01,839 --> 00:20:03,869
I remember it clearly.

264
00:20:04,109 --> 00:20:07,380
You were crying your eyes out
as your mom took her last breath.

265
00:20:08,009 --> 00:20:11,650
I don't care who dies.
I'm going to see the end of this.

266
00:20:12,980 --> 00:20:15,289
And how exactly will you do that?

267
00:20:15,849 --> 00:20:18,559
The Eraser only murdered those
who were infamous...

268
00:20:18,559 --> 00:20:19,619
like the Executioner.

269
00:20:19,789 --> 00:20:21,990
- But?
- But there was an exception.

270
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:24,230
Shimbae.

271
00:20:24,230 --> 00:20:27,259
We'll find the lead
in the Shimbae incident.

272
00:20:27,829 --> 00:20:30,099
We need to find out why...

273
00:20:30,630 --> 00:20:32,470
the Eraser had to kill seven people.

274
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:36,210
Only then will we know the identity
of the Eraser who even had...

275
00:20:36,940 --> 00:20:38,980
to reveal his superpower
in order to kill them.

276
00:20:44,750 --> 00:20:46,220
I need your help.

277
00:20:47,180 --> 00:20:48,549
I've already been kicked out
of this case...

278
00:20:49,720 --> 00:20:51,619
because someone failed
to catch the killer.

279
00:20:51,990 --> 00:20:53,390
Look who's talking.

280
00:20:53,660 --> 00:20:55,359
I risked my life
and chased after him.

281
00:20:55,359 --> 00:20:57,230
I have only myself to blame
for trusting you.

282
00:20:57,230 --> 00:20:59,200
You and your words...
It doesn't matter.

283
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:02,569
It's not your authority that I need.

284
00:21:02,670 --> 00:21:03,900
It's your brain.

285
00:21:04,369 --> 00:21:06,539
Weren't you confident
that you were the brightest?

286
00:21:06,539 --> 00:21:08,670
Of course.
I'm as smart as Sherlock Holmes,

287
00:21:08,670 --> 00:21:10,210
but you have some strengths too.

288
00:21:10,740 --> 00:21:11,740
For example?

289
00:21:11,740 --> 00:21:14,109
You possess knowledge
in criminology which I lack...

290
00:21:14,210 --> 00:21:16,750
and excellent logical reasoning
thanks to your brain.

291
00:21:16,809 --> 00:21:17,980
Are you admitting that I'm the best?

292
00:21:18,980 --> 00:21:21,019
I'm just saying you have
both strengths and weaknesses.

293
00:21:25,759 --> 00:21:27,490
Jin Jae Gyu said something to me
before he died.

294
00:21:29,230 --> 00:21:30,259
What?

295
00:21:32,599 --> 00:21:34,630
The Eraser is hiding...

296
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:39,140
in Dong Baek's past.

297
00:21:41,039 --> 00:21:42,109
What past?

298
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:45,579
"Past"?

299
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:47,740
That's it?

300
00:21:49,750 --> 00:21:51,109
All the leads are useless...

301
00:21:53,819 --> 00:21:57,250
just like my past memories
that I've lost.

302
00:21:59,460 --> 00:22:02,789
What we need to dig into
isn't my past...

303
00:22:02,890 --> 00:22:04,230
but the Shimbae incident.

304
00:22:05,930 --> 00:22:09,400
Do you think that's the past
the Eraser is hiding in?

305
00:22:09,829 --> 00:22:11,940
If he was talking
about your mother's death,

306
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:15,240
then it would've been useless
since everyone knew about that.

307
00:22:15,670 --> 00:22:17,740
- But...
- "But"?

308
00:22:17,910 --> 00:22:19,240
Judging from what I saw...

309
00:22:19,309 --> 00:22:21,240
Shoot him now! It doesn't matter
if I die. Shoot him now!

310
00:22:21,279 --> 00:22:23,849
He would never say something
useless as his last words.

311
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:28,250
I think you're empathizing
with Jin Jae Gyu and his death.

312
00:22:28,250 --> 00:22:30,019
Since the pain I caused you...

313
00:22:31,589 --> 00:22:33,089
is my karma.

314
00:22:34,119 --> 00:22:35,230
Perhaps...

315
00:22:36,789 --> 00:22:39,700
he's referring to intact memories
that didn't get erased.

316
00:22:42,700 --> 00:22:44,769
The Eraser inside...

317
00:22:45,769 --> 00:22:46,970
my intact memories?

318
00:22:48,170 --> 00:22:49,410
How does that make sense?

319
00:22:49,670 --> 00:22:51,980
Maybe you never focused on it
because it's something common,

320
00:22:52,140 --> 00:22:53,680
- or maybe...
- Maybe what?

321
00:22:54,180 --> 00:22:55,549
it was too intense of a moment...

322
00:22:56,380 --> 00:22:58,880
that you couldn't pay attention
to anything else around it.

323
00:22:59,980 --> 00:23:03,019
The Eraser could be hiding
in such a moment.

324
00:23:04,250 --> 00:23:05,859
A moment too intense...

325
00:23:07,859 --> 00:23:10,329
that made me miss everything else?

326
00:23:13,230 --> 00:23:15,400
(Eight years ago)

327
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:22,569
A moment too intense...

328
00:23:23,710 --> 00:23:25,980
that made me miss everything else...

329
00:23:31,009 --> 00:23:33,650
That rooftop when I was 19.

330
00:24:07,119 --> 00:24:08,289
Go do it somewhere else.

331
00:24:14,190 --> 00:24:16,059
They say, taking your shoes off
is a message to others...

332
00:24:16,630 --> 00:24:18,500
asking them to recognize your death.

333
00:24:19,730 --> 00:24:20,829
Is that the case for you too?

334
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:22,900
No, I...

335
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:26,599
Can you do it somewhere else?
This is my spot.

336
00:24:56,869 --> 00:24:57,900
Senior Superintendent Han,

337
00:24:57,900 --> 00:24:59,940
you must be having
a hard time because of Baek.

338
00:25:00,539 --> 00:25:03,839
Hey, look how tired she looks
because of you.

339
00:25:04,009 --> 00:25:06,980
Gosh. He sure has a way
of getting on people's nerves.

340
00:25:09,380 --> 00:25:11,380
- You didn't eat, right?
- Did anyone follow you?

341
00:25:12,849 --> 00:25:15,420
- None.
- We're professionals, you know.

342
00:25:16,289 --> 00:25:17,720
What on earth is going on?

343
00:25:20,390 --> 00:25:22,359
What is this?
Didn't you get her permission?

344
00:25:22,829 --> 00:25:25,160
I was just about to ask
when you came.

345
00:25:29,599 --> 00:25:32,440
Senior Superintendent Han,
we brought some information.

346
00:25:33,869 --> 00:25:36,369
Yes,
it really is something essential.

347
00:25:36,369 --> 00:25:38,309
But because I'm so hungry,

348
00:25:38,640 --> 00:25:40,839
I forgot the most important part.

349
00:25:42,650 --> 00:25:44,210
Please excuse us.

350
00:25:52,259 --> 00:25:53,789
This is an emergency, after all.

351
00:25:58,400 --> 00:26:00,900
We looked through the death cases
from Shimbae City.

352
00:26:01,160 --> 00:26:03,329
Not all of them
lived in Shimbae City,

353
00:26:03,329 --> 00:26:05,140
and they went to different
universities. Isn't it strange...

354
00:26:05,539 --> 00:26:07,569
- they died at the same time?
- So?

355
00:26:08,140 --> 00:26:09,670
We found what they have in common.

356
00:26:10,839 --> 00:26:12,740
- What is it?
- Their entrance exam tutor.

357
00:26:13,039 --> 00:26:14,380
Ever since they were
in kindergarten,

358
00:26:14,380 --> 00:26:18,210
they received
group tutoring only for the rich.

359
00:26:18,920 --> 00:26:20,819
It's something the situation room
figured out already.

360
00:26:21,890 --> 00:26:23,920
Gosh. You're right.

361
00:26:24,519 --> 00:26:28,859
The families of the deceased
are all pretty influential.

362
00:26:29,160 --> 00:26:31,859
Whenever we try to ask a question,
they won't budge.

363
00:26:32,930 --> 00:26:34,529
- Why is that?
- I don't know.

364
00:26:35,599 --> 00:26:37,670
What did you find out, then?

365
00:26:37,730 --> 00:26:39,640
Baek, don't you find it strange?

366
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:42,170
Seven healthy 20-year-olds died,

367
00:26:42,170 --> 00:26:44,509
but not a single family member
is whining about it.

368
00:26:44,940 --> 00:26:46,009
And?

369
00:26:46,079 --> 00:26:50,250
One name, in particular,
made us feel unsettled.

370
00:26:53,549 --> 00:26:55,150
(Name: So Phillip)

371
00:26:56,289 --> 00:26:57,990
- "So Phillip"?
- Yes.

372
00:26:58,819 --> 00:27:01,319
I realized where I've seen it.

373
00:27:01,319 --> 00:27:03,589
- Where?
- Don't you remember?

374
00:27:03,890 --> 00:27:07,430
You sent us to research
some cold cases.

375
00:27:07,759 --> 00:27:09,130
Do you mean the archives of
Seoul Metropolitan Police Agency?

376
00:27:09,269 --> 00:27:10,299
Yes.

377
00:27:10,299 --> 00:27:12,700
It was in one of the official files
of the Special Investigation Team.

378
00:27:13,640 --> 00:27:14,700
(Died due to asphyxiation in
Shimbae City...)

379
00:27:14,700 --> 00:27:16,140
It's a very rare name.

380
00:27:16,539 --> 00:27:17,769
"So Phillip".

381
00:27:17,769 --> 00:27:19,740
(Special Investigation Team
for Cold Cases)

382
00:27:19,740 --> 00:27:20,910
It doesn't make sense.

383
00:27:21,539 --> 00:27:23,509
We didn't do an internal
investigation for that case.

384
00:27:24,049 --> 00:27:25,920
Are you saying
the Special Investigation Team...

385
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:27,150
added the results
of an internal investigation?

386
00:27:28,019 --> 00:27:29,319
There was an internal investigation,

387
00:27:29,750 --> 00:27:32,460
but someone erased all the traces.

388
00:27:32,660 --> 00:27:34,819
It's very difficult to delete...

389
00:27:34,819 --> 00:27:37,059
a police record.

390
00:27:37,259 --> 00:27:39,759
I wonder what they were
worried about to have deleted it.

391
00:27:40,859 --> 00:27:41,970
"Cheon Ki Soo"?

392
00:27:43,369 --> 00:27:45,400
Did you say you're Kim So Mi?

393
00:27:45,940 --> 00:27:47,500
The one from six years ago?

394
00:27:50,369 --> 00:27:51,779
What a strange coincidence.

395
00:27:51,940 --> 00:27:54,339
Cheon Ki Soo was an RIU team leader
at that time...

396
00:27:54,339 --> 00:27:55,980
at the Gyeonggi
Provincial Police Agency.

397
00:27:55,980 --> 00:27:58,380
- You said you know him, right?
- Yes.

398
00:27:58,619 --> 00:28:01,019
I gave him a call earlier, and he
apparently took the day off today.

399
00:28:01,019 --> 00:28:02,519
We scheduled a meeting
tomorrow morning.

400
00:28:02,920 --> 00:28:04,849
Do you think he might be the one
who erased the records?

401
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:06,319
We'll find out.

402
00:28:06,660 --> 00:28:09,690
Whatever it is, we've found
the core of the problem.

403
00:28:09,690 --> 00:28:12,660
Let's see how much
this rotting water will overflow.

404
00:28:13,230 --> 00:28:14,329
Good work.

405
00:28:15,130 --> 00:28:16,400
Gosh.

406
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:17,430
What about me?

407
00:28:17,970 --> 00:28:19,599
What do you think about
a joint investigation team?

408
00:28:23,140 --> 00:28:24,609
You can stay just for tonight.

409
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:30,779
We can't become "The Avengers"
without her.

410
00:28:43,730 --> 00:28:44,890
Gosh.

411
00:28:46,430 --> 00:28:47,960
Stop.

412
00:28:52,470 --> 00:28:53,839
Please don't kill me.

413
00:29:30,569 --> 00:29:31,880
Why are you following me around?

414
00:29:35,880 --> 00:29:37,150
I didn't.

415
00:29:37,750 --> 00:29:38,819
How childish.

416
00:29:39,779 --> 00:29:41,049
Don't do it.

417
00:29:42,650 --> 00:29:43,720
What?

418
00:29:44,220 --> 00:29:45,960
You shouldn't think about
doing the extreme.

419
00:29:48,089 --> 00:29:49,160
"Doing the extreme"?

420
00:29:51,660 --> 00:29:52,759
You make me laugh.

421
00:29:53,900 --> 00:29:56,769
I'm not a pretentious person
like you who makes suicide attempts.

422
00:29:57,599 --> 00:29:58,900
Stop following me around and leave.

423
00:29:59,640 --> 00:30:01,339
I know you went up there
multiple times too.

424
00:30:05,380 --> 00:30:06,440
What?

425
00:30:07,180 --> 00:30:08,339
To die.

426
00:30:10,079 --> 00:30:11,180
Did you see me?

427
00:30:12,250 --> 00:30:14,619
I read your memories.

428
00:30:19,789 --> 00:30:22,559
You're really ridiculous,
although you don't look crazy.

429
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:25,359
You should make your moves
on someone from your own school.

430
00:30:26,630 --> 00:30:27,730
I know you were abused.

431
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:33,099
What?

432
00:30:33,099 --> 00:30:35,099
You were rescued and adopted
just before you were killed.

433
00:30:35,940 --> 00:30:38,940
You're still overwhelmed
by those memories.

434
00:30:41,140 --> 00:30:42,650
Who said such a thing?

435
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:06,069
Baek.

436
00:31:06,839 --> 00:31:08,809
Baek! Baek.

437
00:31:09,509 --> 00:31:10,670
Hurry and get up.

438
00:31:11,309 --> 00:31:14,410
- What?
- Cheon Ki Soo got into an accident.

439
00:31:15,250 --> 00:31:16,380
What accident?

440
00:31:16,380 --> 00:31:17,579
I don't know.
We should go and find out.

441
00:31:19,019 --> 00:31:20,119
Are you going somewhere?

442
00:31:22,119 --> 00:31:24,720
- Let's go together.
- Are we a team now?

443
00:31:28,930 --> 00:31:30,890
Okay. Here comes "The Avengers".

444
00:31:51,309 --> 00:31:52,680
(Mr. Cheon)

445
00:32:02,930 --> 00:32:04,089
Section Chief Cheon.

446
00:32:15,539 --> 00:32:17,009
What happened to you?

447
00:32:17,640 --> 00:32:19,509
I had a concussion,
so I can't remember.

448
00:32:20,410 --> 00:32:21,480
Can't remember what?

449
00:32:21,710 --> 00:32:23,049
No matter how hard I try,

450
00:32:23,549 --> 00:32:25,319
I can't remember his face.

451
00:32:25,980 --> 00:32:29,049
He fell asleep.
I think he was tired.

452
00:32:30,750 --> 00:32:32,359
Yes, we'll be home soon.

453
00:32:33,059 --> 00:32:36,160
Of course, I'll drive safely.
Our son's in the car.

454
00:32:37,029 --> 00:32:38,359
Don't you know your husband?

455
00:32:40,859 --> 00:32:43,730
Do you remember the fried chicken
Jun Young liked last week?

456
00:32:44,170 --> 00:32:45,599
You should order one.

457
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:47,539
Okay, bye.

458
00:32:49,410 --> 00:32:50,509
What a nagger.

459
00:33:09,589 --> 00:33:11,359
Gosh. Jun Young...

460
00:33:12,059 --> 00:33:13,230
Are you okay?

461
00:33:14,660 --> 00:33:17,069
Jun Young. Wake up.

462
00:33:17,230 --> 00:33:20,339
Son! Wake up!

463
00:33:20,900 --> 00:33:23,069
Jun Young! Jun Young!

464
00:33:24,509 --> 00:33:26,140
Wake up.

465
00:33:26,579 --> 00:33:28,750
Son! Wake up!

466
00:33:30,380 --> 00:33:32,450
Jun Young! Wake up!

467
00:33:32,680 --> 00:33:33,720
Jun Young!

468
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:36,890
Jun Young! Son!

469
00:33:36,920 --> 00:33:37,990
Jun Young!

470
00:33:40,059 --> 00:33:42,660
Please help my son out first.
He's in the backseat.

471
00:33:42,660 --> 00:33:44,960
Jun Young! Jun Young!

472
00:33:45,460 --> 00:33:47,559
My son. My son.

473
00:33:47,559 --> 00:33:50,170
Jun Young! Jun Young!

474
00:33:50,430 --> 00:33:52,900
Jun Young! Help my son first!

475
00:33:52,900 --> 00:33:55,339
My son! Jun Young!

476
00:33:57,470 --> 00:33:58,980
Jun Young, no...

477
00:34:00,539 --> 00:34:03,079
What are you doing?
There's someone inside.

478
00:34:03,109 --> 00:34:05,519
I said,
there's someone in the backseat!

479
00:34:05,519 --> 00:34:08,280
My son is still inside!
Get him out right now!

480
00:34:08,519 --> 00:34:10,150
Jun Young!

481
00:34:10,550 --> 00:34:11,920
Jun Young!

482
00:34:12,559 --> 00:34:13,989
Jun Young!

483
00:34:16,630 --> 00:34:18,559
I can't remember his face...

484
00:34:18,590 --> 00:34:20,360
at all.

485
00:34:25,570 --> 00:34:28,670
Please read my memory for me
so I can find him.

486
00:34:54,960 --> 00:34:56,000
Does your head hurt?

487
00:34:57,530 --> 00:35:00,070
No, no. It's nothing. I'm fine.

488
00:35:17,389 --> 00:35:18,590
Jun Young!

489
00:35:18,860 --> 00:35:20,289
Jun Young!

490
00:35:57,030 --> 00:35:58,429
The Eraser! The Eraser!

491
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:01,099
"The Eraser"?

492
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:08,070
The one who only kills garbage?

493
00:36:10,170 --> 00:36:11,269
Was it him?

494
00:36:12,070 --> 00:36:14,940
Why would he kill my son?

495
00:36:16,079 --> 00:36:17,550
Jun Young is a good boy.

496
00:36:19,179 --> 00:36:21,219
He couldn't even kill a bug.

497
00:36:24,789 --> 00:36:26,119
I'll rip that jerk into pieces...

498
00:36:26,619 --> 00:36:28,260
with my own hands.

499
00:36:29,389 --> 00:36:30,460
Give it to me.

500
00:36:35,460 --> 00:36:36,699
That thing in your pocket.

501
00:36:37,230 --> 00:36:38,300
His pocket?

502
00:36:52,579 --> 00:36:53,679
What is this?

503
00:36:54,320 --> 00:36:56,690
- The button from his jacket.
- What are you doing?

504
00:37:01,860 --> 00:37:03,059
Section Chief Cheon swallowed it
after ripping it off.

505
00:37:03,760 --> 00:37:05,230
Just find me a clue.

506
00:37:05,699 --> 00:37:07,659
I'll catch him with my own hands.

507
00:37:10,329 --> 00:37:11,469
There's a design.

508
00:37:12,070 --> 00:37:13,239
"A design"?

509
00:37:14,500 --> 00:37:15,840
It looks like a flame.

510
00:37:24,210 --> 00:37:25,579
I think I know what it is.

511
00:37:34,889 --> 00:37:35,989
What is this?

512
00:37:36,760 --> 00:37:38,530
It must be a torch
inside the flower.

513
00:37:39,530 --> 00:37:40,630
I see it now.

514
00:37:42,900 --> 00:37:43,969
Go ahead.

515
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:48,269
Are you sure you verified it?

516
00:37:49,639 --> 00:37:51,170
Okay. Good job.

517
00:37:53,110 --> 00:37:54,340
It's a symbol for firefighters.

518
00:37:54,639 --> 00:37:55,780
"Firefighters"?

519
00:38:01,780 --> 00:38:03,989
There's a torch inside a flower
that a bird is brooding.

520
00:38:04,119 --> 00:38:05,519
It's the symbol for firefighters.

521
00:38:05,519 --> 00:38:07,219
How do you know all this?

522
00:38:07,460 --> 00:38:08,989
It's all thanks
to the Crime Data Center.

523
00:38:08,989 --> 00:38:10,429
Is there such a thing in Korea?

524
00:38:10,530 --> 00:38:11,659
We're in the process
of constructing it.

525
00:38:12,659 --> 00:38:14,599
We're getting all kinds of help
now that things are rolling.

526
00:38:14,599 --> 00:38:16,000
It was me who initiated it.

527
00:38:17,130 --> 00:38:19,869
It's hard not to respect you,
Senior Superintendent Han.

528
00:38:19,869 --> 00:38:23,440
See? This is what you call
a respectable boss.

529
00:38:23,670 --> 00:38:24,769
What about the initials?

530
00:38:25,210 --> 00:38:26,909
It had an "S" and a "B".

531
00:38:26,909 --> 00:38:30,010
There are eight affiliated
institutes of the fire department...

532
00:38:30,010 --> 00:38:32,380
that can use
"S" and "B" as initials.

533
00:38:33,079 --> 00:38:34,550
But there's no need to look further.

534
00:38:34,820 --> 00:38:36,650
- It's there, isn't it?
- Where?

535
00:38:36,650 --> 00:38:39,489
He was hiding
where he first showed up.

536
00:38:39,690 --> 00:38:41,219
- What?
- What? Then...

537
00:38:42,429 --> 00:38:44,659
Let's go and see
what's waiting for us.

538
00:38:44,760 --> 00:38:46,300
Did you read anything else
in Cheon Ki Soo's memories?

539
00:38:46,300 --> 00:38:49,199
Was it really him who deleted
the case records from 20 years ago?

540
00:38:49,469 --> 00:38:52,170
Also, why did the Eraser
kill Section Chief Cheon's son?

541
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:55,969
- I don't know.
- You don't?

542
00:38:56,210 --> 00:38:59,710
Did you only get to see
the murder scene from last night?

543
00:39:00,409 --> 00:39:02,110
Are you having problems again?

544
00:39:02,480 --> 00:39:03,780
Should we call someone
from the medical team?

545
00:39:03,780 --> 00:39:04,880
Don't mind me.

546
00:39:05,719 --> 00:39:07,119
What if you faint again?

547
00:39:07,119 --> 00:39:09,590
Let him be.
He wants to overwork himself.

548
00:39:09,989 --> 00:39:12,690
You might be young, but
there's no telling who'll go next.

549
00:39:13,659 --> 00:39:16,460
Shouldn't we ask Section Chief Cheon
about the records?

550
00:39:16,630 --> 00:39:19,829
Are you a psychopath?
His only son died last night.

551
00:39:19,829 --> 00:39:21,329
But this case is urgent.

552
00:39:21,329 --> 00:39:23,070
The Eraser will be where
we're going now.

553
00:39:23,530 --> 00:39:25,769
We'll find something,
whether it's his tail or body.

554
00:39:26,940 --> 00:39:28,199
How can you call me a psychopath?

555
00:39:47,360 --> 00:39:48,989
(Shimbae Fire Station)

556
00:39:49,659 --> 00:39:50,659
Let's go.

557
00:39:56,730 --> 00:39:59,300
(Shimbae Fire Station)

558
00:40:00,070 --> 00:40:03,469
We have VIP guests. Hurry
and prepare a welcoming ceremony.

559
00:40:03,710 --> 00:40:06,239
- Yes, sir.
- Wait. We don't have much time.

560
00:40:06,239 --> 00:40:09,150
We're in a rush, so could we
just ask you a few questions?

561
00:40:09,150 --> 00:40:12,050
Firstly,
could you take a look at this?

562
00:40:13,150 --> 00:40:14,349
A button?

563
00:40:14,849 --> 00:40:16,150
What kind of button is it?

564
00:40:16,250 --> 00:40:19,159
It's an important clue, and it has
the symbol of your station on it.

565
00:40:19,760 --> 00:40:21,789
- For a case?
- It's a murder case.

566
00:40:22,019 --> 00:40:24,460
- What?
- I haven't seen buttons like this.

567
00:40:24,889 --> 00:40:27,860
It was on the sleeve of a top.
Maybe it's from a uniform.

568
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:29,300
It's over there.

569
00:40:31,570 --> 00:40:33,239
There are no buttons
on this uniform.

570
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:36,539
- The commemorative suit.
- "The commemorative suit"?

571
00:40:36,539 --> 00:40:38,409
The commemorative suit you get
for serving for 20 years.

572
00:40:38,409 --> 00:40:39,739
Isn't this a button from that?

573
00:40:40,139 --> 00:40:41,780
Yes, you're right.

574
00:40:54,519 --> 00:40:56,860
Can we get the list of people
who have these suits?

575
00:40:57,190 --> 00:41:00,130
Everyone gets it when they reach
their 20th year.

576
00:41:00,130 --> 00:41:01,760
Could I look at your current list
of employees?

577
00:41:03,599 --> 00:41:04,769
Okay.

578
00:41:06,900 --> 00:41:09,409
Sir, how long did you work
in Shimbae City?

579
00:41:09,869 --> 00:41:11,670
About 30 years.

580
00:41:11,769 --> 00:41:15,639
Do you know about the abandoned
factory case from 20 years ago?

581
00:41:16,579 --> 00:41:18,250
Do you mean the one where
several university students died?

582
00:41:18,250 --> 00:41:20,920
- So you know.
- It was huge. Of course, I do.

583
00:41:21,150 --> 00:41:23,019
Why didn't the word get out
about it, then?

584
00:41:23,889 --> 00:41:27,489
I think the families of the deceased
stopped articles from publishing.

585
00:41:27,489 --> 00:41:30,389
They were rich families,
so it would've made more commotion.

586
00:41:31,130 --> 00:41:32,929
I remember hearing a rumor.

587
00:41:33,400 --> 00:41:34,400
What rumor?

588
00:41:35,030 --> 00:41:38,030
That the dead were using drugs.

589
00:41:38,570 --> 00:41:39,670
"Drugs"?

590
00:41:40,099 --> 00:41:41,170
Narcotics.

591
00:41:46,940 --> 00:41:48,880
Did you say Det. Dong Baek is here?

592
00:41:49,010 --> 00:41:50,449
- Yes.
- Why?

593
00:41:50,650 --> 00:41:53,650
You know how we get
commemorative suits, right?

594
00:41:53,949 --> 00:41:57,050
Apparently, one of our suits
was found at a murder scene.

595
00:41:57,449 --> 00:41:59,289
What? One of ours?

596
00:41:59,289 --> 00:42:01,119
You have a suit too, don't you?

597
00:42:01,719 --> 00:42:03,989
Mine disappeared.
I had it taken to the cleaners,

598
00:42:04,260 --> 00:42:05,900
and the owner lost it.

599
00:42:06,460 --> 00:42:08,699
Are you saying those youths
went crazy due to drugs,

600
00:42:08,699 --> 00:42:10,530
and that's why they beat
and killed each other?

601
00:42:12,570 --> 00:42:14,599
But the cause of death
was carbon monoxide.

602
00:42:14,800 --> 00:42:17,869
It's true they died
because of the bonfire,

603
00:42:18,570 --> 00:42:21,139
but it's really because of
the drugs.

604
00:42:21,980 --> 00:42:23,550
They did drugs and killed
each other,

605
00:42:23,550 --> 00:42:24,849
yet it was still covered up?

606
00:42:28,750 --> 00:42:29,820
Here.

607
00:42:33,590 --> 00:42:37,690
There are 9 people who have worked
20 years, including me.

608
00:42:39,960 --> 00:42:42,929
(Years of Service)

609
00:42:43,300 --> 00:42:44,929
It's six if we exclude women.

610
00:42:45,329 --> 00:42:46,570
Can we meet them?

611
00:42:46,699 --> 00:42:48,900
There are only three
who are on duty right now.

612
00:42:55,380 --> 00:42:56,380
What?

613
00:42:56,380 --> 00:42:58,079
Dong Baek's location is up
on social media.

614
00:42:58,079 --> 00:43:00,449
It's Shimbae Fire Station
We'll be there in five minutes.

615
00:43:00,920 --> 00:43:02,650
You better not let him escape.

616
00:43:02,750 --> 00:43:03,889
We'll catch him no matter what.

617
00:43:07,760 --> 00:43:08,860
Step on it.

618
00:43:10,889 --> 00:43:12,699
(Lee Shin Woong)

619
00:43:15,730 --> 00:43:17,099
(Intelligence Division Kim Do Su)

620
00:43:18,070 --> 00:43:19,070
Yes.

621
00:43:19,070 --> 00:43:20,469
This is Inspector Kim Do Su
of the Intelligence Division.

622
00:43:20,469 --> 00:43:21,699
I'm calling to report on
what you ordered.

623
00:43:22,099 --> 00:43:24,539
Det. Dong is currently at
Shimbae Fire Station.

624
00:43:25,170 --> 00:43:26,309
Shimbae Fire Station?

625
00:43:26,510 --> 00:43:28,440
Yes. The prosecution is
on its way to arrest him.

626
00:43:31,110 --> 00:43:32,780
- Keep your eyes on him.
- Yes, sir.

627
00:43:36,550 --> 00:43:38,349
Cancel the rest of my schedules
for today.

628
00:43:38,550 --> 00:43:39,719
Yes, sir.

629
00:43:50,929 --> 00:43:54,099
There's been a poisonous gas leak
at a factory in Simpan-dong.

630
00:43:54,199 --> 00:43:56,210
Emergency phase one.
All units move to the site.

631
00:43:56,710 --> 00:43:57,769
I'm sorry.

632
00:43:58,210 --> 00:43:59,610
I guess you'll have to wait.

633
00:44:00,780 --> 00:44:03,980
Is there anything else you remember
about that incident?

634
00:44:04,309 --> 00:44:07,219
I'm not sure, it's been so long.

635
00:44:08,849 --> 00:44:09,920
Oh, right!

636
00:44:11,190 --> 00:44:13,989
Oh, never mind. It's nothing.

637
00:44:14,219 --> 00:44:15,719
Please tell us anything.

638
00:44:19,130 --> 00:44:22,429
When that accident occurred
at the abandoned warehouse,

639
00:44:22,929 --> 00:44:24,269
I heard a policeman...

640
00:44:25,269 --> 00:44:27,170
arrived at the site
before the firefighters.

641
00:44:29,570 --> 00:44:30,710
And?

642
00:44:31,070 --> 00:44:33,280
But I heard
he didn't do anything...

643
00:44:33,639 --> 00:44:35,639
and just ran away on his own.

644
00:44:36,079 --> 00:44:37,110
Why?

645
00:44:37,110 --> 00:44:38,809
Maybe he didn't
want to get involved.

646
00:44:39,849 --> 00:44:41,280
Was he driving a patrol car?

647
00:44:42,019 --> 00:44:43,389
Probably not.

648
00:44:44,019 --> 00:44:46,659
- Who was the one who saw him?
- What?

649
00:44:47,659 --> 00:44:51,630
Well, that's... I'm not sure.

650
00:44:52,929 --> 00:44:54,030
What's wrong?

651
00:44:54,030 --> 00:44:55,730
The report only came through
the fire station back then.

652
00:44:56,000 --> 00:44:57,730
The police didn't even receive
a report,

653
00:44:57,969 --> 00:45:00,070
so it would only make sense
if the firefighters arrived first.

654
00:45:00,170 --> 00:45:01,639
If we receive an order to move out,

655
00:45:01,639 --> 00:45:03,570
the police receive a call
automatically.

656
00:45:03,840 --> 00:45:05,210
But you said it wasn't a patrol car.

657
00:45:05,869 --> 00:45:06,980
That's right.

658
00:45:07,110 --> 00:45:08,980
The police can't arrive faster
than firefighters.

659
00:45:09,340 --> 00:45:10,980
But if he arrived first
nevertheless...

660
00:45:11,409 --> 00:45:13,449
Does it mean that policeman...

661
00:45:14,550 --> 00:45:15,650
is the Eraser?

662
00:45:19,820 --> 00:45:22,289
If the Eraser is a policeman,
everything adds up.

663
00:45:22,519 --> 00:45:25,460
Was that why he was able to erase
all the records?

664
00:45:26,199 --> 00:45:27,400
It makes sense.

665
00:45:29,500 --> 00:45:30,630
The Eraser?

666
00:45:31,329 --> 00:45:32,400
Wait.

667
00:45:33,739 --> 00:45:35,800
Then what about that button?

668
00:45:36,510 --> 00:45:37,570
What?

669
00:45:37,570 --> 00:45:39,010
We were chasing the button
that fell off...

670
00:45:39,010 --> 00:45:40,780
from the firefighters’ suit
the Eraser was wearing.

671
00:45:41,539 --> 00:45:43,750
But if the Eraser
wasn't a firefighter...

672
00:45:43,750 --> 00:45:45,909
but a policeman who was seen
in that warehouse...

673
00:45:46,619 --> 00:45:50,389
Then who is the real owner
of that firefighters’ suit?

674
00:45:50,619 --> 00:45:51,920
What if the Eraser...

675
00:45:52,550 --> 00:45:55,019
intentionally stole that suit
from here? For what?

676
00:45:59,130 --> 00:46:01,829
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

677
00:46:01,929 --> 00:46:04,699
Who is the person
who saw that policeman?

678
00:46:05,400 --> 00:46:08,539
- Just ignore what I said.
- This is really important.

679
00:46:10,940 --> 00:46:12,909
He's a member from the rescue team.

680
00:46:14,840 --> 00:46:16,250
Is it Rescue Team Leader
Noh Gwang Gyu?

681
00:46:17,710 --> 00:46:18,949
Mr. Noh?

682
00:46:19,750 --> 00:46:22,320
I just asked him about that suit.

683
00:46:22,579 --> 00:46:23,789
I lost it.

684
00:46:23,789 --> 00:46:26,590
I sent it to the dry cleaners,
and they just lost it.

685
00:46:26,690 --> 00:46:28,519
He said he lost that suit.

686
00:46:30,130 --> 00:46:31,190
Where is he now?

687
00:46:31,690 --> 00:46:32,929
He probably went to the site.

688
00:46:33,960 --> 00:46:35,059
He's in danger.

689
00:46:35,400 --> 00:46:36,699
The suit the Eraser was wearing.

690
00:46:39,099 --> 00:46:40,199
It was a clue...

691
00:46:40,940 --> 00:46:42,039
about who he'd kill next.

692
00:46:42,139 --> 00:46:44,539
Order Mr. Noh to come back
immediately.

693
00:46:45,670 --> 00:46:48,480
- What are you talking about?
- I don't know either.

694
00:46:48,579 --> 00:46:50,880
The police said you might be
in danger...

695
00:46:50,880 --> 00:46:51,880
and want you to come back
right now.

696
00:46:52,010 --> 00:46:54,019
What is this nonsense?
Everything we do is dangerous.

697
00:46:54,019 --> 00:46:55,449
Tell them to come see me
it's urgent.

698
00:46:56,820 --> 00:46:57,820
All right.

699
00:46:58,420 --> 00:47:00,019
I can forgive you
if you fail to rescue someone,

700
00:47:00,019 --> 00:47:02,019
but I will never forgive you
if you get hurt. Got it?

701
00:47:02,019 --> 00:47:03,429
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

702
00:47:03,960 --> 00:47:06,130
His life is in danger!

703
00:47:06,559 --> 00:47:09,000
He's the type who never leaves
an accident site.

704
00:47:10,030 --> 00:47:11,099
We should go.

705
00:47:17,570 --> 00:47:19,440
Cheon Ki Soo was in charge of
the case where the Eraser...

706
00:47:19,440 --> 00:47:21,510
killed 7 people in a warehouse
20 years ago.

707
00:47:21,510 --> 00:47:22,510
Right.

708
00:47:22,510 --> 00:47:24,780
And when the Eraser burned
Cheon Ki Soo's son to death,

709
00:47:25,010 --> 00:47:27,679
he apparently stole
Mr. Noh Gwang Gyu's suit.

710
00:47:27,780 --> 00:47:29,480
- Then is that...
- It's a warning on who he'll kill.

711
00:47:30,119 --> 00:47:32,090
He'll kill the owner of that suit?

712
00:47:32,449 --> 00:47:33,690
He's getting rid of a witness.

713
00:47:35,190 --> 00:47:36,530
During the incident
in the warehouse,

714
00:47:36,530 --> 00:47:39,130
Mr. Noh saw a mysterious policeman.

715
00:47:39,829 --> 00:47:42,900
The real Eraser, who arrived
at the site before him.

716
00:47:43,130 --> 00:47:45,699
So he's trying to get rid of
Noh Gwang Gyu since he's a witness.

717
00:47:46,000 --> 00:47:48,239
We need to find him
and read his memory...

718
00:47:49,300 --> 00:47:50,469
There he is!

719
00:47:50,469 --> 00:47:52,670
- Get out of here. We got this.
- Dong Baek!

720
00:47:52,670 --> 00:47:53,840
We'll stop them.

721
00:47:53,840 --> 00:47:54,940
- Hey!
- I'll see you later.

722
00:47:56,179 --> 00:47:59,010
- Hey!
- Catch him! Stop!

723
00:47:59,250 --> 00:48:01,719
- Block them!
- Hey, move!

724
00:48:24,409 --> 00:48:26,110
End the search. Let's move out.

725
00:48:26,110 --> 00:48:27,809
There's someone on the second floor
who needs to be rescued.

726
00:48:27,809 --> 00:48:29,909
She's on the north side
on the second floor.

727
00:48:30,409 --> 00:48:31,809
I'm on the second floor.

728
00:48:32,050 --> 00:48:33,750
- I'll go check.
- Roger.

729
00:48:47,530 --> 00:48:48,659
Help.

730
00:48:49,869 --> 00:48:50,929
Help me.

731
00:48:59,739 --> 00:49:00,809
Are you okay?

732
00:50:45,480 --> 00:50:46,579
Mr. Noh!

733
00:50:47,579 --> 00:50:48,679
Mr. Noh!

734
00:50:49,150 --> 00:50:51,190
Darn. Let's go back in.

735
00:50:51,190 --> 00:50:52,349
Change your oxygen tanks!

736
00:50:54,489 --> 00:50:55,559
He's coming!

737
00:51:05,300 --> 00:51:06,440
Mr. Noh!

738
00:51:11,869 --> 00:51:13,780
- Hey, remove his gear.
- Mr. Noh.

739
00:51:14,079 --> 00:51:15,139
Hurry.

740
00:51:16,480 --> 00:51:17,980
Check his pulse!

741
00:51:20,320 --> 00:51:22,380
- Mr. Noh.
- Mr. Noh!

742
00:51:27,590 --> 00:51:28,789
Dong Baek.

743
00:51:28,860 --> 00:51:30,590
Baek! Are you okay?

744
00:51:30,590 --> 00:51:32,230
Are you insane?
Why did you go in there?

745
00:51:32,460 --> 00:51:34,059
It's him. He was here.

746
00:51:34,059 --> 00:51:36,300
- What?
- He probably didn't get far.

747
00:51:36,300 --> 00:51:38,769
Hurry, move! Hurry!

748
00:51:41,969 --> 00:51:43,039
What are you doing?

749
00:51:44,010 --> 00:51:45,769
His memory from 20 years ago.

750
00:51:50,349 --> 00:51:52,309
- The ambulance is here.
- Move!

751
00:51:52,309 --> 00:51:53,579
Lift him up.

752
00:51:54,250 --> 00:51:55,820
Wait! Wait.

753
00:51:56,349 --> 00:51:57,489
Place him on the stretcher.

754
00:51:58,889 --> 00:52:01,690
No, wait. Wait!

755
00:52:01,820 --> 00:52:03,530
- Let's lift him up.
- 1, 2, 3.

756
00:52:05,130 --> 00:52:06,559
Wait, no.

757
00:52:06,960 --> 00:52:08,500
Aren't you Det. Dong Baek?

758
00:52:08,530 --> 00:52:10,469
We're with the police.
This is an emergency.

759
00:52:34,559 --> 00:52:36,789
His heartbeat and breathing
have returned.

760
00:52:46,570 --> 00:52:47,940
You're unstable right now.

761
00:52:49,670 --> 00:52:50,739
Stop it!

762
00:53:03,019 --> 00:53:05,920
(20 years ago, April 2000)

763
00:53:17,469 --> 00:53:18,630
Are you okay?

764
00:53:21,840 --> 00:53:22,969
Hey!

765
00:53:23,940 --> 00:53:26,010
Kid, are you okay?

766
00:53:38,650 --> 00:53:40,260
Can you call an ambulance...

767
00:53:46,090 --> 00:53:47,159
Hey!

768
00:54:10,389 --> 00:54:13,460
(Shim Sang Ah)

769
00:54:16,190 --> 00:54:17,190
The Eraser.

770
00:54:18,590 --> 00:54:21,829
The Eraser has a scar
on his right arm.

771
00:54:22,300 --> 00:54:24,230
His right arm? Did you see his face?

772
00:54:24,400 --> 00:54:25,530
No.

773
00:54:25,730 --> 00:54:28,699
He had a mask on
so I couldn't see. I don't know.

774
00:54:32,909 --> 00:54:34,010
Your nose his bleeding.

775
00:54:35,610 --> 00:54:38,150
His nose. Inside his nose...

776
00:54:43,849 --> 00:54:46,449
- Det. Dong!
- Det. Dong!

777
00:54:52,460 --> 00:54:53,530
Hey.

778
